<p>The adjacency matrix of a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compl=
ete_graph" title=3D"Complete graph">complete graph</a> contains all ones ex=
cept along the diagonal where there are only zeros. The adjacency matrix of=
 an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Empty_graph" class=3D"mw-redir=
ect" title=3D"Empty graph">empty graph</a> is a <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Zero_matrix" title=3D"Zero matrix">zero matrix</a>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Properties">Properties</h2>=
