.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eigenvalue" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Eigenvalue">=
eigenvalues</a> and an orthogonal <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Eigenvector" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Eigenvector">eigenvector</a> ba=
sis. The set of eigenvalues of a graph is the <b>spectrum</b> of the graph.=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-7" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Adjacency_matrix#cite_note-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span=
>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> It is common to denote th=
e eigenvalues by <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><=
span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display=
: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\di=
